time syncronization from local-host to remote-host using ssh
linux:
on your local host:
ssh <user>@<IP> "date -s \"$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\""
ssh <user>@<IP> "hwclock -w"

for imx8:
ssh root@IMX_IP "date -s \"$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\""
ssh root@IMX_IP "hwclock -w"


windows:

using ps

ssh root@IMX_IP "date -s '$(Get-Date -Format "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss")'"

TL;DR
Here I used command execution over ssh as we can execute command without interactive shell.
